From: nix-on-z <nix-on-z@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] lib/systems/platforms: add s390x-multiplatform definition

Add a platform definition for s390x (IBM Z), similar to existing
definitions for aarch64, riscv, loongarch64, and ppc64.

This provides:
  - linux-kernel configuration with s390-specific target (bzImage)
  - Proper platform selection in the `select` function

Previously, s390x fell through to the empty `{}` default in
platforms.select, meaning no platform-specific linux-kernel
configuration was applied.

diff --git a/lib/systems/platforms.nix b/lib/systems/platforms.nix
index XXXXXXX..XXXXXXX 100644
--- a/lib/systems/platforms.nix
+++ b/lib/systems/platforms.nix
@@ -595,6 +595,16 @@
     };
   };

+  s390x-multiplatform = {
+    linux-kernel = {
+      name = "s390x-multiplatform";
+      target = "bzImage";
+      autoModules = true;
+      preferBuiltin = true;
+      baseConfig = "defconfig";
+    };
+  };
+
   # This function takes a minimally-valid "platform" and returns an
   # attrset containing zero or more additional attrs which should be
   # included in the platform in order to further elaborate it.
@@ -632,6 +642,9 @@
     else if platform.isPower64 then
       if platform.isLittleEndian then powernv else ppc64

+    else if platform.isS390x then
+      s390x-multiplatform
+
     else if platform.isLoongArch64 then
       loongarch64-multiplatform
     else
